OL,3,CParents beg the government not to axe
OL,4,Cdrug for children with rare condition
OL,6,F"A few months in, she started to stand
OL,7,Fagain and crawl around furniture and
OL,8,Fall of a sudden she was back to where
OL,9,Fshe was and it was like, 'oh wow, the
OL,10,Ftreatment works.'
OL,12,F"It's more than just a drug, and it's
OL,13,Fmore than just money on paper. These
OL,14,Fare people's lives.
OL,16,F"And it's so important that we keep
OL,17,Fthe treatment for everybody."
OL,19,FCurrently the treatment costs #75,000
OL,20,Ffor a single dose and is needed every
OL,21,Ffour months.
